  "key_findings": [
    "Diabetes prevalence increases significantly with age, from 2.2% in ages 19-29 to 30.6% in ages 70+",
    "Overall diabetes prevalence in adults 30+ years is 15.5% (5.3 million individuals)",
    "Prediabetes affects 41.1% of adults 30+ years (14.09 million individuals)",
    "Awareness of diabetes is suboptimal at 74.7% overall, and only 43.3% in young adults aged 19-39",
    "Glycemic control (HbA1c <6.5%) is achieved in only 32.4% of diabetic patients",
    "Young adults with diabetes show concerning patterns: 87.1% obesity rate and only 43.3% awareness",
    "Hypertension coexists in 59.6% of diabetic population; only 60.8% achieve BP control",
    "High LDL cholesterolemia affects 74.2% of diabetics; 65.3% achieve LDL control",
    "Only 15.9% of diabetics meet all integrated management targets (HbA1c, BP, and LDL)",
    "Oral hypoglycemic agents are used in 89% of previously diagnosed diabetics; insulin in 6%",
    "Gender differences: men have higher diabetes prevalence (18.1% vs 13.0%) but women have higher cholesterolemia rates",
    "Lifestyle factors: 20.8% current smoking, 22.3% high-risk alcohol consumption in diabetic population",
    "Only 40.2% of diabetics engage in regular physical activity (≥30 min walking, ≥5 days/week)"
  ],
